cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a machine learning approach to solve dynamic multi-objective optimization problems by training an Incremental Support Vector Machine (ISVM) classifier with the past Pareto optimal set (POS) and filtering the solutions of the DMOP through the trained ISVM classifier. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper incorporates the proposed approach into three evolutionary algorithms, namely multi-objective particle swarm optimization (MOPSO), Nondominated Sorting Genetic Algorithm II (NSGA-II), and the Regularity Model-based multi-objective estimation of distribution algorithm (RE-MEDA), to solve dynamic multi-objective optimization problems. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a machine learning approach to solve dynamic multi-objective optimization problems, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with optimization problems, which can be considered as a subfield of discrete mathematics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with dynamic optimization problems, which can be considered as a subfield of systems and control.
